BACKGROUND: Life expectancy has increased worldwide, with India (having 8% who 
are senior citizens), falling into the "Greying Country" category. This ageing 
population constitutes a high-risk oral health group, vis-à-vis impaired manual 
dexterity, cognitive deterioration and unmet treatment needs, which could be 
compounded by psychiatric morbidity.
OBJECTIVE: To assess oral health status and prosthodontic need of ageing 
psychiatric patients.
MATERIALS AND METHOD: One hundred and twenty-five patients, aged 50 years or 
above, admitted to the Department of Geriatric Mental Health, King George's 
Medical University, Lucknow, Uttar Pradesh, India, were examined for 
