disability levels. While 91.3% of the population wearing a prosthesis required 
new dentures, 33.3% of the study population had unfulfilled partial denture need 
and 28.4% had unfulfilled upper/lower complete denture need.
CONCLUSION: Ageing psychiatric subjects require dental education and treatment 
to meet their needs.

