Hepatic angiosarcoma presenting as an acute intraabdominal hemorrhage treated 
with transarterial chemoembolization.

Stambo GW(1), Guiney MJ.

Author information:
(1)Division of Vascular and Interventional Radiology, Department of Radiology, 
St. Joseph's Hospital and Medical Center, Tampa, FL 33607, USA.

Primary malignant neoplasms of the liver are some of the most uncommon 
malignancies in many parts of the world. They include hepatocellular carcinoma 
and stromal tumors such as hepatic angiosarcoma. It is a lethal tumor with life 
